="sc-XxNYO gsQFwr pf-118_ pf-color-scheme-1 pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-dkYRCH hYpqjU"><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-119_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-120_"><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-121_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In the bustling corridors of healthcare facilities, amidst the hustle and bustle of doctors and nurses, there exists a group of dedicated professionals who often work behind the scenes, yet their contributions are no less vital. These are the Allied Health Professionals (AHPs), comprising a diverse array of specialists who play crucial roles in patient care, rehabilitation, and improving health outcomes. Today, we celebrate AHPs Day, a momentous occasion to recognise and honour these unsung heroes of healthcare.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-123_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-124_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-125_ pf-heading-1-h3">Definitions</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/portrait-of-smiling-multi-cultural-medical-team-we-2024-03-05-23-04-57-utc.jpg?v=1709819609" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/portrait-of-smiling-multi-cultural-medical-team-we-2024-03-05-23-04-57-utc.jpg?v=1709819609 1536w" width="1000" height="800" alt="Unlock a World of Learning: How ComplyPlus LMS™ is Revolutionising AHP Education - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Unlock a World of Learning: How ComplyPlus LMS™ is Revolutionising AHP Education - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jQrDum jseZXh pf-127_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-128_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by monkeybusiness via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-130_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><b>Allied Health Professions (AHPs)</b> - A diverse group of healthcare professionals who are not doctors, nurses, or dentists but play crucial roles in healthcare delivery, diagnosis, treatment, and rehabilitation.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-132_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-133_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-134_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/mohdizzuanbinroslan_340f74de-06dd-4abc-b801-6fd3eac90667.jpg?v=1709805351" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/mohdizzuanbinroslan_340f74de-06dd-4abc-b801-6fd3eac90667.jpg?v=1709805351 1536w" width="1000" height="667" alt="Exploring Career Paths: Start Your AHP Journey - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Exploring Career Paths: Start Your AHP Journey - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jQrDum jseZXh pf-136_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-137_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by mohdizzuanbinroslan via Envato Elements</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-139_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-140_ pf-text-1">AHPs constitute a significant portion of the healthcare workforce, making up approximately 6% of the National Health Service (NHS) workforce in the UK.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-142_ pf-text-1">There are over 14 different AHP professions recognised by the NHS, including physiotherapy, occupational therapy, radiography, dietetics, speech and language therapy, and many more.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-144_ pf-text-1">AHPs contribute to a wide range of healthcare settings, including hospitals, clinics, community health centres, schools, and rehabilitation facilities.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-146_ pf-text-1">The World Health Organisation (WHO) recognises the vital role of AHPs in achieving universal health coverage and addressing global health challenges.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-148_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-149_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-150_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recognising the unsung heroes</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/thanks-for-being-our-hero-first-responders-illum-2023-11-27-05-02-17-utc.jpg?v=1709819727" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/thanks-for-being-our-hero-first-responders-illum-2023-11-27-05-02-17-utc.jpg?v=1709819727 1536w" width="1000" height="667" alt="Upgrade Your Skills Today: The Ultimate Guide to Continuing Education - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Upgrade Your Skills Today: The Ultimate Guide to Continuing Education - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jQrDum jseZXh pf-152_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-153_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by maginnislaura via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-155_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">AHPs Day provides an opportunity to shine a spotlight on the invaluable contributions of Allied Health Professionals to healthcare. From helping patients regain mobility through physiotherapy to supporting individuals with speech and language disorders, AHPs play diverse and essential roles in improving the quality of life for millions of people.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-157_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-158_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-159_ pf-heading-1-h3">Highlighting collaboration and innovation</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/hospital-doctors-and-portrait-of-people-on-wall-b-2023-11-27-05-07-05-utc.jpg?v=1709819991" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/hospital-doctors-and-portrait-of-people-on-wall-b-2023-11-27-05-07-05-utc.jpg?v=1709819991 1536w" width="1000" height="667" alt="How to Join Our Healthcare Heroes: A Guide to AHP Training Success - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="How to Join Our Healthcare Heroes: A Guide to AHP Training Success - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jQrDum jseZXh pf-161_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-162_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by YuriArcursPeopleimages via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-164_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">A key theme of AHPs Day is the importance of collaboration and innovation in healthcare delivery. AHPs often work in interdisciplinary teams, alongside doctors, nurses, and other healthcare professionals, to provide holistic and patient-centered care. Through innovation in practice and research, AHPs continuously strive to enhance patient outcomes and experiences.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-166_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-167_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-16